	<!-- message -->
	<p>I'm not sure I'll get a good answer on this, but I'll ask anyway.<br />
<br />
We've started playing a new game for guild events... I'm on the Lanys server and ourselves and our allied guild will play, for lack of a better term, battle chess.<br />
<br />
Here's the thing. A level 60 sham can own... well, pretty much anyone in one on one combat. How or who can defeat a shaman, or have the best chance of defeating him/her?<br />
<br />
Keep in mind, you can not leave the chessboard, so space is limited. We are still tweeking the rules and haven't decided on rules for buffs and such. Right now, only self buffing is allowed, so you can see where that puts a shaman at a distinct advantage. <br />
<br />
As a 56 warrior, I was able to get him down to ~60% health before the dots caught up with me. His pet was a non-issue, only doing about 32pts max damage. I was SoW'd and DS'd (both potions) but other then that had no buffs. A shadow knight, who engaged him next, got him down to 50% before he died. I was able to disarm his epic (and shield, I think) during the battle, so I was able to avoid the epic dot for the first half of the battle.<br />
<br />
I would love to know how to take a shaman down, as I'm sure most people on the PvP servers would. That's the main reason I'm not expecting a good answer...  <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="stick out tongue" smilieid="6" /> <br />
<br />
My personal experience with playing a shaman is limited to the <35 game so far, so I've yet to gather the wealth of personal experience that many of you have. Any help would be appreciated, but I do understand if it never comes. <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="wink" smilieid="5" /></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Xelot Bloodseer<br />
Scaled Mystic of the Ivory Order<br />
Lanys T'Vyl</div>
	
	
