	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Shaman are gimps against melees with high resists. When you can't land slow,  and your dots you are left with a nerfed puppy and your elcrapo melee skills. Especially in an enclosed area with nowhere to run. Any 60+ monk, warrior, pally, sk, ranger with high resists and good jousting skills will own that shaman even if he has malo.<br />
<br />
I've been on the receiving end of monks and rangers with epic and 200+ all resists it's not fun when all your spells bounce and he's jousting you with a slow 2h that smacks you upside the head for 300+ per shot <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
Seriously 200+ resists is not that hard to achieve, you don't need elite gear either. When I don my bag full of resist gear I'm pushing amost 200 in every category except PR and all that gear is easily buyable. Sure you give up a good chunk of HP in exchange but it's worth it against casters.<br />
<br />
Gear off the top of my head:<br />
<br />
Stone of Morid: 30CR 30FR (range item)<br />
Froggy Crown: 20CR 20FR (head)<br />
IGS: 10 all resists (shoulders)<br />
BD bracers: 9 most resists 11 for cold and fire (wrist)<br />
BD rings: 8 all resists (finger)<br />
Lodi shield: 20FR 20CR 10MR (shield or back)<br />
Most epics: 10 on all resists<br />
electrum earrings: 11PR and 11DR and I forget what for the others (ear)<br />
<br />
And many others I'm forgetting. Just remember though that even with good resists that levels make a huge difference, 4 levels below a 60 I think translates into 80 less in all your resists so 200 would equate to 120 if you insist at fighting him at 56 <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
